# Tic-Tac-Toe Game (C++)

A classic console-based Tic-Tac-Toe game written in modern C++.  
This project is focused on clean design, OOP principles, and fun gameplay.

## 🎮 Features

- Two-player game logic  
- Clean UI in terminal  
- Customizable board size  
- Fully modular and expandable

## 📦 Code Quality

- Uses modern C++ features like `std::format`, `std::vector`, and encapsulation  
- Separation of logic into classes (`Game`, etc.)  
- Readable, maintainable, and tested with edge cases

## 🛠️ Upcoming Features

- Player score tracking system  
- Save & load player names and scores using a lightweight database  
- Full leaderboard integration in next update

## 🧠 Learning Purpose

This project is ideal for C++ beginners to understand:
- Class structures
- Encapsulation
- Loops & conditions
- Dynamic memory and vectors

